 Posts: 528<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/03 10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5440.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hmmm</span><hr size=1> Could always get a Reaver too.<br>
<br>
Or Stonebladed Axe of Dismay. <br>
<br>
Either should be in your price range, if you're considering a 2hander.<br>
<br>
As far as a dual wield setup goes ... I used Frostbringer and Praetor's Blade of Debility for a long, long time. The Frosty main, Prae Blade offhand. The DPS wasn't too impressive on the Prae Blade, but the proc was, and really helped me snag aggro from high DPS classes in tanking situations.<br>
<br>
In non-tanking situations, I switched to a velium warsword (the 10/19 one).<br>
<br>
Uh ... I know some people like to pair Guard Captain's Mallet with Frostbringer. The GCM is probably in your price range.<br>
<br>
Also a Spiked Velium Mallet or a Snowchipper are quite popular to pair with Frosty, due to the aggro that their procs usually carry with them.<br>
<br>
Just throwing some more ideas out there for you.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
-Wubao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bulbog>Bulbog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/03 10:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5440.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   2handers</span><hr size=1> Yeah just was going to edit my original post because I just thought of the reaver and the axe.  Both sell less then the widebladed greatsword and the ratios are equal if not better extra stats.  Heh basically like cheap windblades, but wonder how I'd do at holding aggro with them considering they're pure dps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baruchthebarbarianbastard>baruch the barbarian bastard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.diary-x.com/users/translucent/sirnot.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/03 12:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5440.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.diary-x.com/users/translucent/sirnot.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2handers</span><hr size=1> They hold aggro pretty well, unless there are other (hybrid) tanks with the same gear who are casting, taunting, getting better DPS 'cuz of higher level, not watching their aggro in general etc - then you have some problems.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--